text: @realmoney @dougkass @SeabreezeLP Jul 28, 2022 | 09:46 AM EDT DOUG KASS I Do Not Think That Word Means What You Think It Means * From my perch, the Fed did not soft pivot yesterday * Powell's comments (and the interpretation of them) provided tinder to a sharp market advance

* The market's ebullient reaction may be an example of hope over experience * "This just in: You can't take the same actions as everyone else and expect to outperform." "You keep using that word. I do not think it means what you think it means." - Inigo Montoya, Princess Bride
Every administration has an agenda as we all do. But, respectfully, your definition of recession (two consecutive negative real GDP quartes) is not accurate. investopedia.com/terms/r/rec…
